{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 7 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:1",
      "text": "The sons of Issachar: Tola, Puah, Jashub, and Shimron, four.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:2",
      "text": "The sons of Tola: Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeri-el, Jahmai, Ibsam, and Shemuel, heads of their fathers' houses, namely of Tola, mighty warriors of their generations, their number in the days of David being twenty-two thousand six hundred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:3",
      "text": "The sons of Uzzi: Izrahiah. And the sons of Izrahiah: Michael, Obadiah, Joel, and Isshiah, five, all of them chief men;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:4",
      "text": "and along with them, by their generations, according to their fathers' houses, were units of the army for war, thirty-six thousand, for they had many wives and sons.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:5",
      "text": "Their kinsmen belonging to all the families of Issachar were in all eighty-seven thousand mighty warriors, enrolled by genealogy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:6",
      "text": "The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, and Jedia-el, three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:7",
      "text": "The sons of Bela: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri, five, heads of fathers' houses, mighty warriors; and their enrollment by genealogies was twenty-two thousand and thirty-four.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:8",
      "text": "The sons of Becher: Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Eli-o-enai, Omri, Jeremoth, Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth. All these were the sons of Becher;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:9",
      "text": "and their enrollment by genealogies, according to their generations, as heads of their fathers' houses, mighty warriors, was twenty thousand two hundred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:10",
      "text": "The sons of Jedia-el: Bilhan. And the sons of Bilhan: Jeush, Benjamin, Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:11",
      "text": "All these were the sons of Jedia-el according to the heads of their fathers' houses, mighty warriors, seventeen thousand and two hundred, ready for service in war.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:12",
      "text": "And Shuppim and Huppim were the sons of Ir, Hushim the sons of Aher.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:13",
      "text": "The sons of Naphtali: Jahzi-el, Guni, Jezer, and Shallum, the offspring of Bilhah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:14",
      "text": "The sons of Manasseh: Asri-el, whom his Aramean concubine bore; she bore Machir the father of Gilead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:15",
      "text": "And Machir took a wife for Huppim and for Shuppim. The name of his sister was Maacah. And the name of the second was Zelophehad; and Zelophehad had daughters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:16",
      "text": "And Maacah the wife of Machir bore a son, and she called his name Peresh; and the name of his brother was Sheresh; and his sons were Ulam and Rakem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:17",
      "text": "The sons of Ulam: Bedan. These were the sons of Gilead the son of Machir, son of Manasseh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:18",
      "text": "And his sister Hammolecheth bore Ishhod, Abi-ezer, and Mahlah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:19",
      "text": "The sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:20",
      "text": "The sons of Ephraim: Shuthelah, and Bered his son, Tahath his son, Ele-adah his son, Tahath his son,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:21",
      "text": "Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Ele-ad, whom the men of Gath who were born in the land slew, because they came down to raid their cattle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:22",
      "text": "And Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brothers came to comfort him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:23",
      "text": "And Ephraim went in to his wife, and she conceived and bore a son; and he called his name Beriah, because evil had befallen his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:24",
      "text": "His daughter was Sheerah, who built both Lower and Upper Beth-horon, and Uzzen-sheerah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:25",
      "text": "Rephah was his son, Resheph his son, Telah his son, Tahan his son,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:26",
      "text": "Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:27",
      "text": "Nun his son, Joshua his son.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:28",
      "text": "Their possessions and settlements were Bethel and its towns, and eastward Naaran, and westward Gezer and its towns, Shechem and its towns, and Ayyah and its towns;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:29",
      "text": "also along the borders of the Manassites, Beth-shean and its towns, Taanach and its towns, Megiddo and its towns, Dor and its towns. In these dwelt the sons of Joseph the son of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:30",
      "text": "The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and their sister Serah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:31",
      "text": "The sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchi-el, who was the father of Birzaith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:32",
      "text": "Heber was the father of Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and their sister Shua.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:33",
      "text": "The sons of Japhlet: Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These are the sons of Japhlet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:34",
      "text": "The sons of Shemer his brother: Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:35",
      "text": "The sons of Helem his brother: Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and Amal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:36",
      "text": "The sons of Zophah: Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:37",
      "text": "Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran, and Be-era.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:38",
      "text": "The sons of Jether: Jephunneh, Pispa, and Ara.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:39",
      "text": "The sons of Ulla: Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.7.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 7:40",
      "text": "All of these were men of Asher, heads of fathers' houses, approved, mighty warriors, chief of the princes. Their number enrolled by genealogies, for service in war, was twenty-six thousand men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
